                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "PSvV9",
                      "fill": "#60607a",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Custom rules for commit messages, PR titles, and PR descriptions. The dev agent reads these when writing git messages.",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "h5e5T",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "height": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "#0c0c0f",
                      "cornerRadius": 8,
                      "stroke": "#2a2a35",
                      "strokeWidth": 1,
                      "strokeAlignment": "inner",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "padding": [
                        14,
                        16
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "K0FljN",
                          "fill": "#c0c0d0",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "# Commit Messages\n- Use imperative mood: \"Add feature\" not \"Added feature\"\n- Keep subject line under 72 characters\n- No conventional commits prefix (no feat:, fix:, etc.)\n- Focus on WHY not WHAT\n\n# PR Titles\n- Short and descriptive, under 70 characters\n- No prefix tags or ticket numbers in title\n\n# PR Descriptions\n- Brief summary in 1-3 bullet points\n- Include test plan as checklist\n- No auto-generated boilerplate",
                          "lineHeight": 1.5,
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 12,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
